column11:
  We survey combinatorial interpretations of some dozen identities for the
double factorial such as, for instance, (2n-2)!! + Sum_{k=2}^{n}
(2n-1)!!(2k-4)!!/(2k-1)!! = (2n-1)!!. Our methods are mostly bijective.

column5:
13 pages; this version is a complete rewrite of our original article;
  the paper now focuses primarily on the bi-graded case; the title has also
  been changed to reflect the new focus
